{ A backward pawn is a pawn that is behind all pawns of the same color on adjacent files and cannot be safely advanced, making it a strategic weakness.

A backward pawn is defined as a pawn that has fallen behind its neighboring pawns and lacks support from other pawns. This situation typically arises when a pawn cannot advance without being captured, and it often becomes a target for the opponent. For example, if a black pawn is on c6 and there are no pawns on b6 or d6, it is considered backward. }
 *


